body:
This PR introduces the concept of `uiState` into the `index` widget. Previously the `uiState` was only present inside the `RoutingManager`. Now it's a first class citizen of InstantSearch. One of its main usage will be the computation of the `SearchParameters`.

To keep the `uiState` up-to-date at the index level each instance subscribe to the `change` event on its Helper. Each time a widget (e.g. `refine`) or an `index` (e.g. add/remove `setState`) alter the state it triggers an update of the `uiState`.

The `index` now implements the function `getWidgetState`. This function will walk down the tree on each `index` to collect the complete `uiState` for the instance. The function will be useful to get the full `uiState` from the top level InstantSearch instance.

The format of the `uiState` changed. Each indices is now scoped under its identifier which is by default the name of the index (it will change to be able to target multiple times the same index). We've made this change because it's way simpler to work with a structure like this one. We don't have to branch to detect whether or not we are at the root (versus the one inside React InstantSearch). Any other ideas/alternatives are welcome!

**Edit**: With this new shape of `uiState` that would be nice to detect whether or not we are in a single/multi index context. That would allow us to preserve the current shape of URL with a single index. We can investigate when we adapt the routing mechanism.

**Old format**:

```
{
  "refinementList": {
    "brand": ["Apple"]
  }
}
```

**New format:** non back-ward compatible

```
{
  "instant_search": {
    "refinementList": {
      "brand": ["Apple"]
    }
  },
  "instant_search_price_asc": {
    "query": "iPhone",
    "menu": {
      "categories": "Phone"
    }
  }
}
```

**Alternative format:** back-ward compatible (React InstantSearch)

```
{
  "refinementList": {
    "brand": ["Apple"]
  },
  "indices": {
    "instant_search_price_asc": {
      "query": "iPhone",
      "menu": {
        "categories": "Phone"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
